<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>agem — AI coding agent for the terminal</title>
  <meta name="description" content="agem reads your code, writes patches, runs commands, and bridges to Discord and WhatsApp — all from a persistent daemon.">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css">
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <div class="container">
    <a href="index.html" class="logo"><span class="dim">$</span> <span class="accent">agem</span></a>
    <button id="hamburger" aria-label="Toggle navigation">
      <span></span><span></span><span></span>
    </button>
    <nav id="nav-menu">
      <a href="index.html">Home</a>
      <a href="features.html">Features</a>
      <a href="install.html">Install</a>
      <a href="docs.html">Docs</a>
      <a href="compare.html">Compare</a>
      <a href="changelog.html">Changelog</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/Purple-Druid/AgentEmerald" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gh-link">GitHub ↗</a>
    </nav>
  </div>
</header>

<main>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>An AI coding agent for the terminal — and beyond.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        <code>agem</code> reads your code, writes patches, runs commands, and bridges to Discord and WhatsApp —
        all from a persistent daemon that keeps working after you close the window.
      </p>

      <div class="install-block">
        <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Purple-Druid/AgentEmerald/main/install.sh | sh</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="install.html" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started →</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/Purple-Druid/AgentEmerald" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-outline">View on GitHub ↗</a>
      </div>

      <p class="trust-bar">MIT License · GitHub account only · macOS · Linux · Windows</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Feature Highlights -->
  <section id="features">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Everything you need. Nothing you don't.</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">agem is built terminal-first, designed for developers who live in the shell — with integrations that let you reach your codebase from anywhere.</p>
      <div class="feature-grid">
        <div class="feature-card">
          <span class="icon">🖥️</span>
          <h3>Terminal-first TUI</h3>
          <p>Streaming markdown, live tool sidebar, diff previews before any write, full keyboard control.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <span class="icon">⚙️</span>
          <h3>Always-on daemon</h3>
          <p>Persistent gateway with WebSocket + HTTP API, SQLite sessions, job scheduler, hot reload.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <span class="icon">📱</span>
          <h3>Chat platform bridges</h3>
          <p>Discord, Telegram, WhatsApp, Matrix. Reach your codebase from anywhere, any device.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <span class="icon">🔑</span>
          <h3>No extra API keys</h3>
          <p>GitHub Copilot or GitHub Models. <code>gh auth login</code> is all it takes to get started.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <span class="icon">🛡️</span>
          <h3>Safety built in</h3>
          <p>Four execution modes. Every tool call classified. Diff previews. Approval dialogs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <span class="icon">🧩</span>
          <h3>MCP integration</h3>
          <p>Connect any MCP server via config. Stdio or SSE. Auto-loaded on start.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Comparison teaser -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="compare-teaser">
        <h2>How does agem stack up?</h2>
        <span class="muted">agem brings a unique combination of terminal UX, always-on daemon, and messaging bridges.</span>
        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Feature</th>
                <th class="center">agem</th>
                <th class="center">Claude Code</th>
                <th class="center">Cursor</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Terminal TUI</td>
                <td class="center badge">✅</td>
                <td class="center badge">✅</td>
                <td class="center badge">❌</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Always-on daemon</td>
                <td class="center badge">✅</td>
                <td class="center badge">❌</td>
                <td class="center badge">❌</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Chat bridges</td>
                <td class="center badge">✅</td>
                <td class="center badge">❌</td>
                <td class="center badge">❌</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Free (GitHub account)</td>
                <td class="center badge">✅</td>
                <td class="center badge">❌</td>
                <td class="center badge">❌</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Open source (MIT)</td>
                <td class="center badge">✅</td>
                <td class="center badge">❌</td>
                <td class="center badge">❌</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <a href="compare.html" class="full-link">Full comparison →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>

<!-- CTA Band -->
<div class="cta-band">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Ready to ship faster?</h2>
    <a href="install.html" class="btn btn-primary">Install agem →</a>
  </div>
</div>

<footer>
  <div class="container">
    MIT License · <a href="https://github.com/Purple-Druid/AgentEmerald" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open source on GitHub</a> · Built by Damien Hodgkin
  </div>
</footer>

<script src="js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
